	<text>He said that the party could nominate a replacement candidate.</text>
</context>
<context>
	<score>0.46176946</score>
	<text>Governorship and state assembly elections were held on 14 April , while the presidential and national assembly elections were held a week later on 21 April . Umaru Yar&apos;Adua won the highly controversial election for the ruling People&apos;s Democratic Party (PDP) and was sworn in on 29 May .</text>
